prefercite.head: Preferred Citation
prefercite.p: Archibald R. Rowzie papers, 1795-1941. Accession 52812. Personal Papers collection, The Library of Virginia, Richmond, Virginia.

bioghist.head: Biographical Information
bioghist.p: Archibald Ritchie Rowzie was born ca. 1830 in Essex County, Virginia to Richard Rouzie (1789-1870) and Janet Ritchie Rouzie. He married Catharine "Kitty" W. Lewis in 1854. Rowzie trained as a medical doctor and served as an Assistant Surgeon during the Civil War. He also served as Postmaster for Mount Landing, Virginia before and after the Civil War, as well as teaching and farming. Rowzie died 15 September 1902.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Content
scopecontent.p: Papers, 1795-1941 (bulk 1831-1941), of Archibald R. Rowzie (ca. 1830-1902) of Essex County, Virginia, consisting of accounts, bills, correspondence, genealogical information, medical publications, photographs, and receipts. Also includes material collected by various Rowzie family members including Roll and Minute Books for the Patriotic Order Sons of America, Washington Camp No. 32 1914-1921.

arrangement.head: Arrangement
arrangement.p: This collection is arranged alphabetically by folder title.
